title: Sheet 7I
publication_title: James Ensor: The Temptation of Saint Anthony
content:
<section class="osci-tk-epub-section body" id="body">This drawing extends from folio 6H/I above, completing the exaggeratedly large wheel of a cart. A small artist’s patch formerly covered the anus of the figure being crushed by the wheel. There are several pinholes in the upper area of the sheet; this suggests that at one time it was pinned to another surface, perhaps together with folio 6H/I. The present sheet’s right edge is irregularly cut where it was separated from a larger folio. SMC/KJN
